description: The team must work with a group of psychotic outlaws. Trouble doesn't even begin to describe what happens next.
name: Episode Ten

description: With the team trapped, Five must save the day ... but all actions have consequences.
name: Episode Eleven

description: Eph changes his appearance to leave the city while Nora is left as the reluctant parent for Zack. Dutch and Nora make a deal with Justine to secure Fet's release from jail.
name: Quick and Painless

description: A freak accident mutates a modern day citizen into a mutant known as Muckman.
name: The Noxious Avenger

description: Slash and The Mutanimals are captured by The Shredder to test a newly created mind control serum on them.
name: Clash of the Mutanimals

description: Mikey and Casey meet a skateboarding gecko who looks to befriend them. But is this new mutant all he says he is?
name: Meet Mondo Gecko

description: When Karai is experimented on with Shredder's mind control serum, he orders her to eliminate Splinter, The Turtles, and their friends.
name: The Deadly Venom

description: The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles are accidentally transported to the past where they cross paths with a familiar ninja clan.
name: Tale of the Yokai

description: Leonardo decides to sneak into Shredder's lair alone, and winds up facing the biggest mutant threat yet.
name: Attack of the Mega Shredder!

description: After getting in an accident, Donatello begins to slowly lose his intelligence.
name: The Creeping Doom

description: Eph concocts a plan to make and distribute a bioweapon. Gus realizes Angel can be an unlikely ally, and Kelly comes after Nora and Zack.
name: Identity

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Anoko wa Kawaii Mochiya no Musume)

Tamako works at her father's mochi shop, and along with her friends she enjoys a comfortable life at Tama-ya, the local shopping district. A talking bird suddenly interrupts their little slice of paradise, and things begin going downhill from there.
name: That Girl's the Cute Daughter of a Mochi Shop Owner

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Koi no Hanasaku Barentain)

Tamako is leading a Valentine's Day movement in the shopping district, but her father is opposed to the whole thing. Mochizo decides to make a commercial to help Tamako win over her stubborn father.
name: The Love-in-Bloom Valentine's

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kru na Anoko ni Atchitchi)

Asagiri is the "cool girl" to Tamako and her friends. Dera falls for Asagiri at first sight, and pursues her at every chance. Little do they know, Asagiri is painfully shy and often finds it difficult to put her thoughts into words.
name: Hot Hot Hot Over That Cool Girl

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Chsana Koi, Saichatta)

It's festival time at Usagiyama, and while spirits are soaring and everyone dons their festive wear, Anko refuses to be a part of any of it. Most would say she hates festivals, but there's something that's keeping her from joining in.
name: A Small Love Has Bloomed

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ichiya o Tomoni Sugoshitaze)

While Tamako and her friends prepare for the big swimming field trip at school, Mochizo decides to tell Tamako how he feels about her. Dera decides to lend a helping hand, only to encounter a protective Midori intent on keeping Tamako safe.
name: We Spent a Night Together

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ore no Sesuji mo Kttaze)

With a heat wave in full swing and the shopping district's attendance waning, Tamako plans to host a spine chilling haunted house to rouse attention from potential shoppers.
name: It's Chilled Even My Spine

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Anoko ga Oyome ni Ichatta)

The mysterious girl turns out to be Choi, a fortune teller from the Southern Islands who is on the same mission as Dera. Fearing her wrath, Dera tells Choi that he was trapped here. Choi gets to know the citizens of the shopping district.
name: That Girl's Become a Bride

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Niwatoridato wa Iwasene)

Dera has become to fat to fit into a birdhouse Kanna has lovingly crafter for him so a food restriction is put in place. Choi continues acclimating herself to her surroundings, becoming closer with Tamako and the girls along the way.
name: I Won't Let You Call Me a Chicken

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Utatchaunda, Koi no Uta)

Dera has become to fat to fit into a birdhouse Kanna has lovingly crafter for him so a food restriction is put in place. Choi continues acclimating herself to her surroundings, becoming closer with Tamako and the girls along the way.
name: I Will Sing Love's Song

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Anoko no Baton ni Hana ga Saku)

The school culture festival is approaching and the Baton Club has somehow found themselves with a great timeslot on the main stage. Midori struggles to come up with good choreography for the club.
name: Flowers Bloom on That Girl's Baton

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Masaka Ano Musume ga Purinsesu)

Word gets around that Tamako MAY be a princess, while Tamako herself focuses on earning more loyalty points to get a medal from the shopping district.
name: I Never Thought That Girl Would be a Princess

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kotoshi mo Mata Kuretetta)

With the entire shopping district taking an interest in the big news, Tamako feels unsure of how she feels. With a proposal from Mechya to deal with, Tamako reminisces about how much her little shopping district has meant to her throughout her life.
name: This Year, Too, Has Come to a Close

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ichi Gt Yumeno Danchi)

Welcome to the Yumeno Apartments, where Haruki Nakano lives out his everyday life with his four sisters.
name: Building One: The Yumeno Apartments

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ni Gt Futago no Shukudai)

Uzuki and Satsuki do their best to finish their homework. Their assignment? A report on their family members!
name: Building Two: The Twins' Homework

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (San Gt Mutsuki no Sugao)

Mutsuki is bright and beautiful, and diligent to top it all off. But she shows a different side in front of Haruki...
name: Building Three: Mutsuki's True Colors

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yon Gt Karraisu)

The grocery shopping must be done, so the Nakano siblings get together to conquer the week's shopping list.
name: Building Four: Curry and Rice

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Go Gt Satsuki no Anime Tokei)

Satsuki and Haruki have an unexpected hobby in common. And Satsuki never misses a beat.
name: Building Five: Satsuki's Anime Clock

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Nozoki Daisakusen)

Five boys newly enrolled in a formerly all-girls school, already having difficulty connecting with the girl students, run afoul of the school's "Underground Student Council" and face strict disciplinary measures.
name: The Peep Job

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Shiri Sugiteita Otoko)

Hana is embarrassed when Kiyoshi sees her in a compromising position. Kiyoshi becomes desperate to keep his date with Chiyo, and searches for a way to get out of prison in time to meet her. Gakuto has plans of his own.
name: The Man Who Viewed Too Much

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Daifunshutsu)

With Meiko's attention divided between two groups, Kiyoshi is able to widen the escape hole enough to let him through in time for his date. An already-suspicious Shingo gets an eyeful of more than he bargained for.
name: A Mighty Spurt

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Watashi o Sum ni Tsuretette)

After committing a heinous offense against Mari, Gakuto receives a drastic punishment from Meiko. Kiyoshi and Gakuto work desperately to break Kiyoshi out of the prison by having him impersonate a girl.
name: Take Me Out To the Sumoland

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Gakuen ichi no uragirio)

Kiyoshi returns from his breakout, but must face the music with Gakuto and the others when the truth comes to light. Chiyo reconsiders her reaction to Kiyoshi, and decides to give him a second chance.
name: The School's Number One Most Treacherous Man

description:
Proper Japanese Title:

Mari introduces the DTO plan to Hana, and they begin plotting ways to drive the boys out of school. Shingo leads the others boys in shunning Kiyoshi, but Meiko has plans to drive an even deeper wedge between them.
name: Vengeance Is Hana's

description: Ash is baaack! 30 years after his last Deadite fight, badass monster hunter Ash Williams unleashes the Evil in an act of carelessness, bringing Deadite mayhem into his life again.
name: El Jefe

has_staff_review.name: Ash vs Evil Dead Episode #101 - "El Jefe"

description: A highly dysfunctional blended family is forced together when they realize a reported virus is actually the onset of the undead apocalypse.
name: Pilot

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Roku Gt Shimai no Kakezan)

Multiplication is a fundamental skill! Everyone has to learn their multiplication tables in elementary school. If they dont...
name: Building Six: The Siblings Multiplication

deck:
A masked vigilante known as Casey Jones is striking down criminals all across the city. The Turtles cross paths with him when he mistakes them for criminals and Martian invaders.

Meanwhile Krang has created a robotic bug with the ability to take control of the machines so he can build a device known as the Supersize Knucklehead. Casey and the turtles team-up to stop them.
name: Casey Jones - Outlaw Hero

description: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.
name: Operation Tin Man

description: Raven is cursed to be nice; meanwhile, Starfire is about to marry a pot of chili.
name: Nean

description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip, so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.
name: Campfire Stories

description: Raven just wants some piece and quiet for once, and accidentally makes a magical deal that eliminates all sounds.
name: And the Award for Sound Design Goes to Rob

description: Tired of the Titans, The Hive agrees to take a day off and avoid engaging with their foes - if possible.
name: The HIVE Five

description: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.
name: The Return of Slade

description: Can the Titans master the four New Year's traditions in order to break the cycle of bad years?
name: More of the Same

description: Robin uses a prism to split each Titan into the five facets of their personalities so he can choose only the best parts for his ideal crime fighting team.
name: Some of Their Parts

description: Robin decides to become a cat so that Starfire will finally love him.
name: Cat's Fancy

description: After being defeated due to poor leg strength, Raven and the Titans work out their lower bodies and become the League of Legs.
name: Leg Day

description: When Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, against Raven's advice the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.
name: Dignity of Teeth

description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.
name: Croissant

description: Setrakian and Fet use Fitzwilliam's info to attack the Master, but a mysterious new player arrives. Dutch receives a surprise guest. Eph returns to NYC frustrated but energized to go after the one person responsible for killing his friends.
name: The Born

description: Best friends Mordecai and Rigby take mundane tasks and problems at their boring job to fantastical places.
name: Dumptown USA

description: After Benson doesn't take home the award for Park Manager of the Year, the guys want to make him feel like a winner.
name: The Parkie Awards

description: Rigby ruins Maellard's fancy lunch, and now he or Benson has to write a letter of resignation.
name: The Lunch Club

description: Margaret really wants to host a weekly segment on the nightly local news.
name: Local News Legends

description: Benson wants to prove that he was right about the date of the Dome Experiment.
name: The Dome Experiment

description: While Madison struggles to keep Nick from crippling withdrawal, Travis ventures out to find his son before the city of Los Angeles falls.
name: So Close, Yet So Far

has_staff_review.name: Fear the Walking Dead Episode #102: "So Close, Yet So Far"

deck: Mari McCabe is on the run from the Flash and Arrow
name: Episode 1

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Nana Gt Danchi de Pru Biraki)

It might be a little early to go to the beach, but that's not going to stop these siblings from having some fun in the water.
name: Building Seven: The Apartment Complex's Pool Opening?!

description: Tired of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans try their hand at spicing up their food.
name: Spice Game

description: Eph must protect Zack against a surprise intruder into Red Hook. Gus convinces the Guptas to make a difficult choice. Fet and Setrakian set out to acquire the Lumen but discover they are not the only potential buyer.
name: Intruders

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Bikinim wa bikinimdeatte bikinide wanai)

As they continue on their world-saving adventure, Fighter, Paladin, Mage, and Dark Elf decide to upgrade their armors to the latest version after a difficult battle in a dungeon. But what is the difference between bikini armor, and a normal bikini?
name: It's Not a Bikini If It's Armor.

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ysha no tabidachi ni wa dshitemo hitsuyna mono ga aru)

The four heroes are summoned to an audience with the king. The world is in peril, and his royal highness orders them to go on a journey to save it. Fighter asks him for the money they need to help them prepare, but
name: A Quest Needs Money to Rest

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yuusha to Iedomo Ikite Ikanakereba Naranai no de Aru)

The Special Hero Dispensation Act gives heroes the right to legally take items from treasure chests and dressers in town. When the four adventurers run out of money and can't continue their journey, they use this law to start invading the townspeople's houses, but
name: Even Heroes Have Needs

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yuusha Taru Mono Mikaeri wo Motomete wa Ikenai)

The heroes need a key to get through a cave and continue with their adventure. But the arrogant mayor of the town has it, and he won't hand it over unless they complete the tasks he gives them. Fighter decides that this must be a trial for the heroes, and ends up doing the mayor's chores.
name: A Hero Needs No Reward

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Itsuka tsukau to omotte iru mono wa daitai saigomade tsukawanai)

The party needs the magic Ice Staff to defeat the dungeon boss. But it's too expensive, and so they decide to sell items in their inventory to get the money. The four even sell their elixirs, but
name: Saving Things That Go Unused

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ysha to wa genkai ni idomi, sore o koeru monodearu)

Women, and only women, are being attacked in a nearby forest. The heroes go to try and find whoever's responsible. They're faced with a veteran opponent who hides himself in the forest while attacking with many different spells. Their armor is almost entirely blown off, but they continue to fight...
name: Heroes Overcome the Impossible

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Sakaba de deatta nakama ni kadona kitai o suru no wa kinmotsu)

The party visits a tavern to find a new comrade. When Dark Elf complains that none of the candidates are any good, the rest of the party turns to her and says, You don't get to talk! What happened when Dark Elf first joined the party?
name: Allies From Taverns May Disappoint

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Bken no nakaba ni aratana nakama ga kuwawaru koto wa yoku aru hanashi)

Two new girls want to join the party: Hunter and Valkyrie. The two are both such unique characters that they may not be usable for anything, so the party has them fight each other, and promises to take the winner
name: Every Journey Finds New Friends

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hachi Gt Shimai desu ne)

Do all twins look the same? Join the Nakanos as they look through some family history.
name: Building Eight: Definitely Siblings

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Kizuita Toki ni wa Hajimatteita toiu Hanashi)

Since club participation is required in their school, Yui, Iori, Himeko, Taichi, and Aoki choose to join the Student Cultural Society. They begin to get to know each othera little too well! Yui and Aoki claim to have swapped bodies!
name: A Story That Had Already Begun Before Anyone Realized It

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ramia no Iru Nichij)

Due to a clerical error, protagonist Kurusu becomes the host family to students of different species. One student, lamia girl, Mia, is touched by Kurusu's kindness, and makes bold moves on him.
name: Everyday Life with a Lamia

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Hp to Kentaurosu no Iru Nichij)

Kimihito is suddenly kidnapped by Papi the Harpy. The naive Papi begins innocently bathing in public. Miia is jealous when she sees this, and the two get in a fight. Just then they hear the voice of a girl stuck in a tall tree... On another day, as Kimihito returns home from a shopping trip, a centaur girl leaps from around the corner and crashes into him. With massive breasts and a ponytail, Centorea was searching the town for a master to serve according to centaur tradition. In order to catch the man who snatches a purse right before her eyes, she chases after him with Kimihito riding on her back...
name: Everyday Life with a Harpy and Centaur

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Abunai Jij na Nichij)

The Kurusu family's homestay grows to three in the blink of an eye. Not yet accustomed to living with three monster girls, Kimihito's life is a series of disasters. When Miia sees Kimihito helping others, her jealousy boils over. With each girl loving Kimihito in their own way, they eventually come to blows!
name: Everyday Life Under Dangerous Circumstances

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Suraimu no Iru Nichij)

A strange object appears in the pot and eats Miia! The culprit is an amorphous slime. Centorea weilds her blade against the attacking slime to protect Kimihito, but both of them end up covered in slime. They take a bath to wash the slime off, where they sink the slime on a wild rampage is search of water into the tub...! Papi names the slime Suu, and she begins living with them.
name: Everyday Life with a Slime

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ningyo no Iru Nichij)

The girls' strategy meeting to protect Suu is interrupted by the sudden arrival of the Interspecies Exchange Security Squad. Believing they have come to capture Suu, the girls leave Kimihito and flee with Suu. Kimihito hurries after them and runs into a noble-looking girl in a wheelchair.
name: Everyday Life with a Mermaid

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Dappi to Sanran Suru Nichij)

Miia trains to become Kimihito's bride by throwing herself into cooking. However, she seems absent minded and burns both of her hands. She is out of sorts because she is shedding. She cries that she is useless and can't even shed by herself, but Kimihito cheers her up and offers to help her shed.
name: Everyday Life with Shedding and Egg Laying

description:
Proper Japanese Title: MON (MON to Arakune no Iru Nichij)

A standoff involving a high school girl held hostage takes place at a doujin shop. The Orc Pioneer Federation demands that "orc x female knight" adult comics be made mainstream. Smith's "MON" arrives at the scene. They are a special squad assembled to handle crimes committed by non-human species!
name: Everyday Life with MON and an Arachne

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Taich Fury na Nichij)

Rachnea quickly becomes a member of the Kurusu household. Miia is jealous of her overly-friendly manner, but not even she stands a chance against Rachnea's mature composure. Centorea claims not to be opposed to living together, but when Rachnea's round the clock sexual tormenting of Kimihito doesn't stop, she can't keep her emotions in check!
name: Everyday Life in Poor Health

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Sake no Shioyaki)

Murasaki Wakako is a twenty-seven year old working lady. As per her daily routine, she rewards herself for a hard day at work by bar-hopping in search of the best alcohol and seafood the world has to offer. On tonight's menu, she has some crispy fried salted salmon and cold sake. This ultimate combination makes her purr in satisfaction.
name: Fried Salted Salmon

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Tori no Karaage)

Freshly-fried food is out of this world! Tonight's menu is comprised of stuff that Wakako has strong cravings for every now and then, fried chicken and chilled beer. The beer goes perfectly with the chicken as it washes down the fresh'n'juicy aftertaste. Dig in while it's hot!
name: Fried Chicken

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Ankimo Ponzu)

Drown your sorrows in alcohol! On tonight's menu is a comfort meal, monkfish liver in ponzu accompanied by hot sake. After stuffing her face with the liver, Wakako washes it down with the sake. Even the worst days at the office can seem like no big deal after this.
name: Monkfish Liver in Ponzu

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Unikureson)

A local specialty! On tonight's menu is Hiroshima's famous sea urchin cresson and beer. When placed on a pan with melted butter, the urchins seem like they break out into a dance. And what else could go better with this working-class meal than a cold beer?
name: Sea Urchin Cresson

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Yakitori)

The perfect plan! On tonight's menu is some charcoal-grilled yakitori and draft beer. With a glass of beer in hand, Wakako stuffs her face with the skewered yakitori and immediately washes it down with her drink. In that smoky ambience, this sip feels divine.
name: Yakitori

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Asari no Sakamushi)

After a tiring day's work, have some relaxing steamed clams and sake. The perfectly-prepared soup soaks into the clams and heals your exhausted body and soul. The sake goes down smoothly, perhaps aided by the feelings of gratitude towards the seven seas for providing this delicacy.
name: Steamed Clams

description:
Proper Japanese Title: (Potato Salad)

Nothing beats a good potato salad! On tonight's menu is the common man's best friend, potato salad, accompanied by oolong tea highball. The down-to-earth drink and potatoes form a top-class B+ duo, filling both your belly and your soul.
name: Potato Salad

description: Proper Japanese Title: (Gouya Chanpuru)
name: Goya Chanpuru

description: Stuck inside because of bad weather, the Titans play rainy day games after Robin convinces them that indoor activites will cheer up the clouds and make the rain stop.
name: I'm the Sauce

description: Rigby always gives Mordecai the worst birthday gifts, but this year it's going to be different.
name: Birthday Gift

description: Proper Japanese Title: (gendai niokeru shikaku wo chuushin to shita bunka no kenkyuu)
name: The Study of Modern Visual Culture

description: Proper Japanese Title: (shouhi to yuukyou niyoru gendai seishounen no hikaku bunrui)
name: Comparative Classification of Consumption and Diversion among Modern Youth

description: Proper Japanese Title: (chiiki bunka shinkou no mondai ten to sono kouseki)
name: The Issue of Regional Cultural Advancement and its Merits

description: Proper Japanese Title: (funsou to kasou no ika niyoru shinri teki shouheki no shouka sayou)
name: The Sublimated Process of Mental Blocks Regarding the Dissimilation Between Dress and Costume

description: Proper Japanese Title: (jiritsu koudou ni miru haiseki to juyou no kyoukai)
name: The Boundary Between Rejection and Acceptance Seen in Autonomous Behavior

description: Proper Japanese Title: (SABUKARUCHAA wo meguru tasha to no kankeiron)
name: Subculture and its Circular Relationship to Others Surrounding It

description: Proper Japanese Title: (taijin kankei niokeru koudou sentaku no tokuchou)
name: Characteristics of Action and Decisions in Personal Relationships

description: Proper Japanese Title: (ryousan gata seizou katei ni okeru hikaku kenkyuu)
name: Comparative Research of the Mass Production Process

description: Proper Japanese Title: (tokushu heisa joukyou ka ni okeru setsumei gimu no umu nitsuite)
name: Concerning Whether Explanation is Obligatory Under Special Circumstances
